reviewer_texts.Clarity & Rigor:
The proof presents a sophisticated argument combining algebraic topology, geometric group theory, and surgery theory. The strategy of using the Equivariant Euler Characteristic obstruction (Fowler) as the primary barrier, and backing it up with L-theory (Farrell-Jones) for the vanishing cases, is sound in principle.

However, from a **Clarity & Rigor** perspective, the treatment of the "vanishing Euler characteristic" case (Case B) is insufficient. The proof asserts that L-theory provides a contradiction but treats the mechanism as a black box, lacking the necessary detail to constitute a rigorous argument at the graduate level.

